Four Hundred Souls|edited  Ibram X. Kendi,Keisha N. Blain|One World|A compendium featuring 90 writers covering 400 years of African-American history.
Think Again|Adam Grant|Viking|An examination of the cognitive skills of rethinking and unlearning that could be used to adapt to a rapidly changing world.
Just As I Am|Cicely Tyson with Michelle Burford|HarperCollins|The late iconic actress describes how she worked to change perceptions of Black women through her career choices.
A Promised Land|Barack Obama|Crown|In the first volume of his presidential memoirs, Barack Obama offers personal reflections on his formative years and pivotal moments through his first term.
Unmasked|Andy Ngo|Center Street|A former writer for the online magazine Quillette gives his perspective on the activist movement antifa.
Greenlights|Matthew McConaughey|Crown|The Academy Award-winning actor shares snippets from the diaries he kept over the last 35 years.
Caste|Isabel Wilkerson|Random House|The Pulitzer Prize-winning journalist examines aspects of caste systems across civilizations and reveals a rigid hierarchy in America today.
Untamed|Glennon Doyle|Dial|The activist and public speaker describes her journey of listening to her inner voice.
Becoming|Michelle Obama|Crown|The former first lady describes how she balanced work, family and her husband’s political ascent.
How To Be An Antiracist|Ibram X. Kendi|One World|A primer for creating a more just and equitable society through identifying and opposing racism.
When Harry Met Minnie|Martha Teichner|Celadon|The CBS Sunday Morning correspondent develops a bond with the ailing owner of a dog she agrees to adopt.
Mike Nichols|Mark Harris|Penguin Press|A biography of the award-winning theater and film director who was also half of the seminal improv duo with Elaine May.
Let Me Tell You What I Mean|Joan Didion|Knopf|A collection of 12 pieces written between 1968 and 2000 that includes observations on the underground press and the act of writing.
A Swim In A Pond In The Rain|George Saunders|Random House|A collection of essays examining the functions and importance of works of fiction.
Like Streams To The Ocean|Jedidiah Jenkins|Convergent|The author of “To Shake the Sleeping Self” explores eight subjects that he believes give life meaning.
